04519nam a22007455i 9780231544009DE-B159720200826040535.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||200826t20172017nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a(OCoLC)984688175  a97802315440097 a10.7312/ghal182062doi  a(DE-B1597)482785  a(OCoLC)975032211  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY 7aPOE0090002bisacsh04a891.4/3911 aGhalib, Mirza Asadullah Khan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aGhalib :bSelected Poems and Letters /cMirza Asadullah Khan Ghalib. 1aNew York, NY : bColumbia University Press, c[2017] 4c©2017  a1 online resource (224 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aTranslations from the Asian Classics00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction: Ghalib’s Life and Times -- tPart One: Ghazals -- tPart Two: Ghazal Verses -- tPart Three: Other Genres -- tNotes -- tAppendix 1. Ghalib’s Comments on His Own Verses -- tAppendix 2. Ghalib Concordance, with Standard Divan Numbers -- tGlossary of Technical Terms and Proper Names -- tBibliography -- tIndex -- tUrdu Text 0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis selection of poetry and prose by Ghalib provides an accessible and wide-ranging introduction to the preeminent Urdu poet of the nineteenth century. Ghalib's poems, especially his ghazals, remain beloved throughout South Asia for their arresting intelligence and lively wit. His letters—informal, humorous, and deeply personal—reveal the vigor of his prose style and the warmth of his friendships. These careful translations allow readers with little or no knowledge of Urdu to appreciate the wide range of Ghalib's poetry, from his gift for extreme simplicity to his taste for unresolvable complexities of structure.Beginning with a critical introduction for nonspecialists and specialists alike, Frances Pritchett and Owen Cornwall present a selection of Ghalib's works, carefully annotating details of poetic form. Their translation maintains line-for-line accuracy and thereby preserves complex poetic devices that play upon the tension between the two lines of each verse. The book includes whole ghazals, selected individual verses from other ghazals, poems in other genres, and letters. The book also includes a glossary, the Urdu text of the original poetry, and an appendix containing Ghalib's comments on his own verses.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 7aPOETRY / Asian / General.2bisacsh1 aCornwall, Owen T. A.1 aPritchett, Frances08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066255908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook Package 2017z978311065472108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2017z978311054330840uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/ghal1820640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231544009423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231544009.jpg  a978-3-11-054330-8  CUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2017b2017  a978-3-11-064982-6  Asian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Package  a978-3-11-065472-1  CUP eBook Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-066255-9  CUP eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK